---
import CTAButton from "../ui/CTAButton.astro";
import NavigationHint from "../ui/NavigationHint.astro";
---

<!-- What We Do Section -->
<section
  id="solution"
  class="snap-none-mobile pt-24 pb-20 md:py-20 md:min-h-[100dvh] flex flex-col px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8"
>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto flex-1 flex flex-col justify-center">
    <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-center mb-16">
      Philosophic conversation
    </h2>
    <div
      class="prose prose-lg sm:prose-xl prose-invert max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-16"
    >
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-300 mb-8">
        This is not therapy and not coaching. It is an <a
          href="/listen/dwelling"
          class="text-amber-400 hover:text-amber-300 no-underline"
          >enjoyment layer</a
        > for your knowledge deep down — facilitating engagement with what you already
        have, and what you're learning, with no agenda of its own.
      </p>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-300 mb-8">
        Through conversation, we draw out your reserves — trace them back to
        their roots, follow them outward to where they reach into other domains
        of your life. What's unarticulated becomes available. What's been
        private turns out to speak to something that's important, and not just
        for you.
      </p>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-300">
        And unlike a library of digital files — fixed, distinct, unchanged no
        matter how many times you return — what you know deep down is alive. It
        reorganizes as you engage with it, deepens, branches, becomes higher
        resolution. You don't dwell with what you know and separately grow. The
        dwelling on what you know is growing too — which means this is also an
        enjoyment layer on what you're learning, on what's new and still working
        its way in.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
      <div class="text-center">
        <div
          class="w-16 h-16 bg-blue-500/20 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-6"
        >
          <svg
            class="w-8 h-8 text-blue-400"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
          >
            <path
              stroke-linecap="round"
              stroke-linejoin="round"
              stroke-width="2"
              d="M8 12h.01M12 12h.01M16 12h.01M21 12c0 4.418-4.03 8-9 8a9.863 9.863 0 01-4.255-.949L3 20l1.395-3.72C3.512 15.042 3 13.574 3 12c0-4.418 4.03-8 9-8s9 3.582 9 8z"
            ></path>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Power listening</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-300">
          Not advice, not direction. We certainly don't have all the answers.
          Generative questions and fortifying curiosity — accompaniment that
          helps you hear and say something important about what's important
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="text-center">
        <div
          class="w-16 h-16 bg-amber-500/20 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-6"
        >
          <svg
            class="w-8 h-8 text-amber-400"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
          >
            <path
              stroke-linecap="round"
              stroke-linejoin="round"
              stroke-width="2"
              d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z"></path>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Natural growth</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-300">
          You respond to what's important by growing and by knowing — it's your
          natural response and the only adequate response. The ongoing
          engagement with your reserves of knowledge deep down is what makes the
          most of what you are and what you can be.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="text-center">
        <div
          class="w-16 h-16 bg-emerald-500/20 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-6"
        >
          <svg
            class="w-8 h-8 text-emerald-400"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
          >
            <path
              stroke-linecap="round"
              stroke-linejoin="round"
              stroke-width="2"
              d="M9.663 17h4.673M12 3v1m6.364 1.636l-.707.707M21 12h-1M4 12H3m3.343-5.657l-.707-.707m2.828 9.9a5 5 0 117.072 0l-.548.547A3.374 3.374 0 0014 18.469V19a2 2 0 11-4 0v-.531c0-.895-.356-1.754-.988-2.386l-.548-.547z"
            ></path>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Treasure the mind</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-300">
          We take your mind seriously — setting aside devoted time with expert
          accompaniment to discover the wisdom that has yet to be articulated,
          and that may well be important not only to you
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Let's talk CTA -->
    <div class="mt-8 text-center">
      <CTAButton variant="secondary" />
    </div>

    <NavigationHint href="#about" text="About Tam" />
  </div>
</section>
